content_1: Three additional outbreaks of the highly pathogenic H5N1 avian influenza virus have been reported.  One occurred at Qinghai Lake in Hai Hanan prefecture where 2,361 Pallas?s gulls (also known as the greater black-headed gull) were found dead.  At the Shuangheer wetland, Inner Mongolia, 300 black-necked grebes died.  415 brown-headed gulls and bar-headed geese were found dead at the Galongcuo bird island in Tibet.  The exact clade of the strains and source of the virus is unknown. Avian Influenza in Poultry
